These scenarios include self-propagating malware (e.g. network worms), or unavoidable common use scenarios where code execution occursáwithoutáwarnings or prompts. "No Data" á= There are no stopped instances that are scheduled for patching within the next 72 hours. Only running instances can be patched, stopped instances will not be auto-started.

<visual-title>

</visual-title>

<visual-subtitle>A Key Performance Indicator for patch compliance is the % of EC2 Instances that are covered by a patching maintenance window. Monitor this metric over time to understand if you are taking sufficient action to improve patch compliance in your organization.</visual-subtitle>

<visual-title>
  <inline font-size="20px">Patched in the last 7 days withá</inline>
  <inline color="#23d194" font-size="20px">no outstanding patches</inline>
</visual-title>
<visual-subtitle>Instances that were recently patched, and have no outstanding patches, generally indicates that a successful patch activity occurred.</visual-subtitle>

<visual-title>
  <inline font-size="20px">Patched in the last 7 days with</inline>
  <inline color="#951c1e" font-size="20px">á> 0 outstanding patches</inline>
</visual-title>

Instances that were recently patched, but have outstanding patches, may indicate:
  • a failure during patching;
  • a patch was released after the instance was patched;
  • a patch was previously excluded by a patch baseline, but that patch is no longer excluded.
